          "main.py": "age_text = input()\n\nprint(age_text)\nprint(type(age_text))\n\n# Try changing the input to 25.\n# Even though it looks like a number, input() gives you text first.\n",
          "notes.md": "Key idea:\n\ninput() always returns a string.\n\nIf you want to do math, convert it first with int() or float().\n"
